com.vmware.vcenter.lcm.discovery

Interface AssociatedProducts

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AssociatedProductsTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AssociatedProductsStub

    public interface AssociatedProducts
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, AssociatedProductsTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The AssociatedProducts interface provides options to list, add, modify, and delete VMware products associated with vCenter Server. Some products can be auto-detected by the system while others can be added manually.

    • Method Detail

      • list

        AssociatedProducts.ListInvocation list()
        Retrieves a list of all associated VMware product deployments with vCenter Server in the environment. The list contains both product deployments discovered automatically and deployments registered manually through the API.

        Invocation Result:
        List of all the registered products with vCenter.

        Returns:
        instance of AssociatedProducts.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Error - If there is some unknown internal error. The accompanying error message will give more details about the failure.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires VcLifecycle.View.

      • create

        AssociatedProducts.CreateInvocation create(AssociatedProductsTypes.CreateSpec spec)
        Associates a VMware product with vCenter Server manually. The product must be taken from the product catalog API.

        Invocation Result:
        Identifier of the newly-added product. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.vcenter.lcm.product.

        Parameters:
        spec - Info creation specification.
        Returns:
        instance of AssociatedProducts.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        AlreadyExists - if this version is already added
        InvalidArgument - if the spec argument is not allowed
        Error - If there is some unknown internal error. The accompanying error message will give more details about the failure.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires VcLifecycle.View.
